  <section id="what-is-osteoporosis">
    <h2>What Is Osteoporosis?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Osteoporosis means bones become weak and fragile.</li>
      <li>Fractures can happen even from minor falls or lifting.</li>
      <li>Wrist, hip, and spine are the most common sites.</li>
      <li>It often progresses without symptoms until a fracture occurs.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="treatment">
    <h2>Why Treatment Matters</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Reduces the risk of future fractures by 20‚Äì50%.</li>
      <li>Improves mobility, independence, and overall well-being.</li>
      <li>Treatment includes lifestyle changes, supplements, and medication.</li>
      <li>Therapies are tailored to each person based on tests and risk factors.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="study">
    <h2>About This Study</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You received a Pocketcard or QR-Code with this website link.</li>
      <li>This study helps improve care for patients with wrist (radius) fractures.</li>
      <li>Your participation helps shape better services and raise awareness.</li>
      <li>All data is collected securely and anonymously.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="next-steps">
    <h2>Your Next Steps</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Book a visit at a Fracture Liaison Service (FLS) Clinic.</li>
      <li>Get a full bone health check-up including lab tests and bone scans.</li>
      <li>Push notifications can remind you of upcoming appointments.</li>
      <li>Use the self-assessment tool to check your fracture risk.</li>
      <li>Watch a short video to learn more about osteoporosis (coming soon).</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="privacy">
    <h2>Data Privacy & Consent</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Your information is secure and encrypted.</li>
      <li>No names or personal identifiers are stored.</li>
      <li>You can withdraw from the study at any time with no impact on care.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

